Look, before Lindbergh 
could cross the Atlantic,

40:29.094 --> 40:31.011
he took off from one of those runways.

40:31.096 --> 40:33.430
Do you ever wonder why they called it
the Spirit of St. Louis?

40:33.515 --> 40:35.307
- No.
- Well...

40:42.899 --> 40:46.443
<i>Do you know how fucked
this place is now?</i>

40:46.528 --> 40:48.570
I am the one thing, the one thing,

40:48.655 --> 40:52.491
preventing this place
from being totally fucked in the ass.

40:58.748 --> 41:01.208
Sometimes they just need to vent.

41:03.878 --> 41:07.297
Please, for the love of God,
can I fire the next one?

41:07.757 --> 41:11.718
- Miss Barnes, thank you for joining us.
- I'm here to be fired, right?

41:12.720 --> 41:14.972
Well, we're here to talk 
about your future.

41:15.056 --> 41:18.142
You don't have to sugarcoat it.
I get the drill.

41:18.226 --> 41:20.018
What are they offering?

41:20.103 --> 41:22.813
Inside the packet, you'll find a clearly
worked out severance package.

41:22.897 --> 41:24.940
Give me the bullet points.

41:25.733 --> 41:27.317
It's actually pretty good.

41:27.402 --> 41:29.653
Three months' pay, 
six months' medical

41:29.737 --> 41:32.656
and a full year of placement services
through our company, CTC.

41:32.740 --> 41:35.534
Placement services. 
That's generous.

41:38.705 --> 41:41.081
Commonly, it takes one month 
of searching for every $10,000

41:41.166 --> 41:42.332
you expect to earn in salary.

41:42.417 --> 41:44.918
So, I could be looking for a while.

41:45.003 --> 41:47.087
- Not necessarily.
- Don't even sweat it.

41:47.172 --> 41:49.173
I'm pretty confident about my plans.

41:50.216 --> 41:51.758
- Really?
- Yeah.

41:52.343 --> 41:55.179
There's this beautiful bridge
by my house.

41:55.930 --> 41:57.931
I'm gonna go jump off it.

41:59.684 --> 42:00.934
Natalie.

42:01.269 --> 42:02.436
Hey!

42:02.770 --> 42:04.146
Natalie!

42:13.489 --> 42:15.574
People say these things all the time.

42:15.658 --> 42:17.242
It's part of the trade.

42:17.327 --> 42:18.827
- They do?
- Yeah.

42:18.912 --> 42:21.580
I mean, they say crazy things.

42:22.040 --> 42:23.874
They get worked up.

42:24.918 --> 42:26.835
She was really calm.

42:27.295 --> 42:29.463
I think that's a good sign.

42:30.298 --> 42:31.798
So, they don't ever actually do it?

42:31.883 --> 42:33.884
No. No, it's just talk.

42:34.886 --> 42:36.470
How do you know? 
Do you follow up?

42:36.554 --> 42:39.640
I mean, no.
Nothing good's gonna come of that.

42:41.017 --> 42:43.101
I wouldn't worry about it.

42:44.479 --> 42:46.021
This is what we do, Natalie.

42:46.105 --> 42:49.983
We take people at their most fragile,
and we set them adrift.

42:55.240 --> 42:57.324
You ready to go back in?

42:58.117 --> 43:00.410
All right, let's go. 
Come on.

43:44.747 --> 43:47.416
No, I'm fine. 
Tell me something sweet.

43:48.876 --> 43:49.835
I'll be back soon.

43:49.919 --> 43:53.171
I'm not really sure how long
this whole exercise is supposed to last.

43:53.256 --> 43:55.716
No, I don't even think of him that way.
He's old.

44:36.924 --> 44:37.966
I'm done?

44:38.051 --> 44:40.052
I wasn't expecting this. 
Not at all.

44:40.136 --> 44:41.136
Just like that?

44:41.220 --> 44:45.015
I'm disappointed that I've given
so much of my life...

44:45.099 --> 44:46.433
This is not fair.

44:46.517 --> 44:48.894
There are people that are gonna be
way more qualified than me now.

44:48.978 --> 44:51.271
I don't know what to do when I wake up
in the morning tomorrow.

44:59.155 --> 45:00.739
Are you okay?

45:02.575 --> 45:05.410
- Are we going?
- Yeah.

45:23.012 --> 45:25.931
<i>This is how I start every day of my life.</i>

45:28.226 --> 45:31.395
Now, this is gonna be a little difficult,
so stay with me.

45:31.479 --> 45:33.397
You have a new backpack.

45:33.481 --> 45:36.900
Only this time,
I want you to fill it with people.

45:37.151 --> 45:40.529
Start with casual acquaintances,
friends of friends,

45:41.155 --> 45:42.906
folks around the office.

45:42.990 --> 45:44.074
And then you move into the people

45:44.158 --> 45:46.159
that you trust with
your most intimate secrets.

45:46.244 --> 45:48.912
Your cousins, your aunts, your uncles,

45:48.996 --> 45:51.873
your brothers, your sisters, your parents.

45:53.000 --> 45:57.504
And finally your husband, your wife,
your boyfriend or your girlfriend.

45:59.006 --> 46:01.508
You get them into that backpack.

46:03.052 --> 46:06.263
Don't worry. I'm not gonna ask you
to light it on fire.

46:08.182 --> 46:09.808
Feel the weight of that bag.

46:10.893 --> 46:13.103
Make no mistake,
your relationships are the heaviest

46:13.187 --> 46:15.230
components in your life.

46:16.941 --> 46:20.277
Do you feel the straps
cutting into your shoulders?

46:21.904 --> 46:27.200
All those negotiations and arguments
and secrets and compromises.

46:31.038 --> 46:33.832
<i>You don't need to carry all that weight.</i>

46:34.208 --> 46:36.626
<i>Why don't you set that bag down?</i>

46:38.671 --> 46:41.047
Some animals were meant
to carry each other,

46:41.132 --> 46:43.800
to live symbiotically for a lifetime.

46:44.594 --> 46:46.970
Star-crossed lovers,
monogamous swans.

46:47.054 --> 46:49.055
We are not those animals.

46:51.726 --> 46:54.311
The slower we move, the faster we die.

46:54.395 --> 46:56.563
We are not swans.

46:58.191 --> 46:59.733
We're sharks.

47:13.915 --> 47:15.373
- <i>Never?</i>
- <i>No.</i> 

47:15.958 --> 47:17.417
- <i>Ever?</i>
- <i>No.</i>

47:18.127 --> 47:20.420
- You never want to get married?
- Nope.

47:20.505 --> 47:22.839
- Never want kids?
- Not a chance.

47:22.924 --> 47:24.758
- Ever?
- Never.

47:25.635 --> 47:28.261
- Is that so bizarre?
- Yes.

47:28.721 --> 47:30.138
Yes, it is.

47:30.640 --> 47:33.058
I just don't see the value in it.

47:33.893 --> 47:36.394
- All right, sell it to me.
- What?

47:36.479 --> 47:38.271
Sell me marriage.

47:39.941 --> 47:42.442
- Okay, how about love?
- Okay.

47:43.819 --> 47:46.363
Stability, just somebody
you can count on.

47:46.447 --> 47:48.448
How many stable marriages
do you know?

47:48.533 --> 47:51.451
Somebody to talk to,
someone to spend your life with.

47:51.536 --> 47:55.539
I'm surrounded by people to talk to.
I doubt that's going to change.

47:56.415 --> 47:58.792
How about just not dying alone?

47:59.460 --> 48:00.585
Starting when I was 12,

48:00.670 --> 48:03.338
we moved each one of my grandparents 
into a nursing facility.

48:03.422 --> 48:05.215
My parents went the same way.

48:05.299 --> 48:07.801
Make no mistake, we all die alone.

48:08.135 --> 48:12.806
Now, those cult members in San Diego
with the Kool-Aid and the sneakers,

48:13.307 --> 48:15.058
they didn't die alone.

48:15.142 --> 48:17.769
I'm just saying there are options.

48:20.773 --> 48:22.232
Fuck.

48:23.693 --> 48:25.277
Brian left me.

48:32.827 --> 48:34.286
All right.

48:36.455 --> 48:38.331
Okay, okay. 
All right.

48:40.334 --> 48:41.793
All right.

48:44.088 --> 48:45.213
Yeah.

48:51.554 --> 48:52.679
Hey.

48:56.767 --> 48:59.978
Natalie, this is Alex, my friend.
This is Natalie.

49:01.439 --> 49:03.481
I should give you both a moment.

49:03.566 --> 49:05.317
No. No, that's fine.

49:05.401 --> 49:08.111
I'm fine. 
It's a pleasure to meet you.

49:09.071 --> 49:12.866
Maybe we should just all go up
to our rooms and freshen up.

49:13.326 --> 49:14.618
Or maybe a drink?

49:14.702 --> 49:15.785
Now you're talking.

49:19.332 --> 49:21.791
He broke up with you
over text message?

49:21.876 --> 49:25.170
It's kind of like firing someone
over the Internet.

49:26.964 --> 49:28.173
What a weaselly prick.

49:28.257 --> 49:30.425
Yeah. But what does that make me?

49:30.509 --> 49:33.053
- Someone who falls for a prick.
- We all fall for them.

49:33.137 --> 49:35.930
Pricks are spontaneous, 
they're unpredictable, and they're fun.

49:36.015 --> 49:39.309
And then we're surprised
when they turn out to be pricks.

49:39.393 --> 49:41.478
I followed him to Omaha.

49:41.562 --> 49:42.979
You did?

49:43.564 --> 49:44.814
I had a job waiting for me
in San Francisco

49:44.899 --> 49:47.400
when he got an offer from ConAgra.

49:48.861 --> 49:51.029
He said we could start a life together.

49:52.239 --> 49:53.740
So, I followed him.

49:53.824 --> 49:55.283
To Nebraska?

49:58.454 --> 50:00.580
I thought I'd be engaged by now.

50:01.415 --> 50:02.832
No offense.

50:02.917 --> 50:05.293
- None taken.
- That's all right.

50:06.587 --> 50:09.673
When I was 16,
I thought by 23 I'd be married,

50:10.424 --> 50:11.466
maybe have a kid,

50:11.550 --> 50:14.594
corner office by day,
entertaining at night.

50:14.679 --> 50:16.596
I was supposed to be driving
a Grand Cherokee by now.

50:16.681 --> 50:19.599
Yeah, life can underwhelm you that way.

50:20.101 --> 50:23.019
I mean, where did you think
you'd be by...

50:26.273 --> 50:27.440
It doesn't work that way.

50:27.525 --> 50:29.567
At a certain point,
you stop with the deadlines.

50:29.652 --> 50:31.403
It can be a little counterproductive.

50:31.487 --> 50:33.488
I don't want to say anything
that's anti-feminist.

50:33.572 --> 50:36.908
I really appreciate everything
that your generation did for me.

50:36.992 --> 50:38.493
- It was our pleasure.
- Well done.

50:38.577 --> 50:41.538
But sometimes it feels like
no matter how much success I have,

50:41.622 --> 50:44.249
it's not gonna matter
until I find the right guy.

50:45.167 --> 50:47.585
You really thought this guy
was the one?

50:48.170 --> 50:49.963
I could have made it work.

50:50.423 --> 50:53.174
He... He really fit the bill.

50:53.759 --> 50:55.760
- You know?
- The bill?

50:55.845 --> 50:57.804
White-collar, college grad,

50:58.264 --> 51:02.809
loves dogs, likes funny movies,
6'1", brown hair, kind eyes,

51:02.893 --> 51:07.021
works in finance but is outdoorsy,
you know, on the weekends.

51:08.524 --> 51:14.821
I always imagined he'd have a single 
syllable name like Matt or John or Dave.

51:16.407 --> 51:18.241
In a perfect world, he drives a 4Runner.

51:18.325 --> 51:22.162
And the only thing he loves
more than me is his golden Lab.

51:23.497 --> 51:25.165
And a nice smile.

51:28.043 --> 51:30.336
- What about you?
- Let me think.

51:33.174 --> 51:35.216
You know, honestly,
by the time you're 34,

51:35.301 --> 51:38.052
all the physical requirements
just go out the window.

51:38.137 --> 51:42.015
I mean, like, you secretly pray
that he'll be taller than you,

51:43.017 --> 51:44.642
and not an asshole would be nice.

51:44.727 --> 51:47.604
Just someone who enjoys my company,
comes from a good family.

51:47.688 --> 51:50.398
Because you don't think about that
when you're younger.

51:50.483 --> 51:53.276
I don't know. 
Someone who wants kids.

51:54.111 --> 51:56.196
Likes kids. Wants kids.

51:57.239 --> 51:59.866
Healthy enough to play with his kids.

52:03.120 --> 52:06.247
Please let him earn more money
than I do.

52:06.332 --> 52:09.292
You might not understand that now,
but believe me, you will one day.

52:09.376 --> 52:12.212
Otherwise, that's a recipe for disaster.

52:13.881 --> 52:16.466
And hopefully some hair on his head,

52:16.884 --> 52:20.386
but, I mean, even that's not
a deal breaker these days.

52:23.808 --> 52:25.391
A nice smile.

52:27.520 --> 52:30.730
Yeah, a nice smile.
Nice smile just might do it.

52:33.734 --> 52:35.735
Wow, that was depressing.

52:37.530 --> 52:40.114
- I should just date women.
- Tried it.

52:40.741 --> 52:42.909
We're no picnic ourselves.

52:46.497 --> 52:48.957
I don't mind being married to my career,

52:50.209 --> 52:53.837
and I don't expect it to hold me in bed
as I fall asleep.

52:57.716 --> 53:00.051
I just don't want to settle.

53:00.553 --> 53:04.389
You're young. Right now you see settling 
as some sort of a failure.

53:04.473 --> 53:07.141
It is, by definition.

53:07.935 --> 53:12.313
Yeah. But by the time someone is right 
for you, it won't feel like settling.

53:12.398 --> 53:13.857
And the only person left to judge you

53:13.941 --> 53:17.652
will be the 23-year-old girl
with a target on your back.

53:21.365 --> 53:23.908
So, what's the plan for the evening?

53:24.201 --> 53:28.454
Well, we were gonna hit that party
for the tech conference at the hotel.

53:28.539 --> 53:30.248
I didn't know you could just attend those.

53:30.332 --> 53:32.542
I thought you had to be registered.

53:32.626 --> 53:34.002
Well, technically, I don't think

53:34.086 --> 53:36.796
- it's open to the public.
- Just gonna stop by.

53:37.214 --> 53:39.299
You're gonna crash it?

53:39.884 --> 53:41.968
- They throw a really nice party.
- Well, they have more money

53:42.052 --> 53:44.470
- than they know what to do with.
- And they have a good time, usually.

53:44.555 --> 53:46.806
No, no, I get it. I'm in.

54:07.786 --> 54:09.370
Jennifer Chu?

54:09.997 --> 54:11.998
- Shit!
- It'll be fine.

54:34.688 --> 54:36.356
Doing all right?

54:38.150 --> 54:40.276
Yeah. This was a great idea.

54:42.446 --> 54:44.155
You're so pretty.

54:45.115 --> 54:48.368
You're exactly
what I wanna look like in 15 years.

54:48.786 --> 54:50.578
Thank you, Natalie.

